1
00:00:14,020 --> 00:00:17,060
(Yoo Yeon Seok)

2
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:20,060
(Esom)

3
00:00:20,690 --> 00:00:24,930
(Kim Kyung Nam)

4
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:28,970
(Kim Mi Kyung, Jeon Seok Ho, Son Yeo Eun, Lee A Rin)

5
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:33,270
(Choi Kwang Il, Jung Seung Gil, Yeon Je Hyung)

6
00:00:44,080 --> 00:00:47,990
(Phantom Lawyer)

7
00:00:48,020 --> 00:00:50,019
(Supported by Ministry of Culture, Sports and KOCCA)

8
00:00:50,020 --> 00:00:51,489
(All people, places, and events in this drama are fictional.)

9
00:00:51,490 --> 00:00:52,966
(Child actors filmed safely with guardians.)

10
00:00:52,990 --> 00:00:53,990
(All scenes involving animals were staged...)

11
00:00:53,991 --> 00:00:55,631
(and filmed safely by welfare standards.)

12
00:00:57,100 --> 00:01:00,000
(Episode 13)

13
00:01:01,330 --> 00:01:04,370
- Excuse me, where's Shin Yi Rang? - You're with Shin Yi Rang, right?

14
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:06,670
- Yes. - I'm so sorry.

15
00:01:07,270 --> 00:01:10,010
He was already unconscious when he was brought in.

16
00:01:23,320 --> 00:01:24,320
No.

17
00:01:33,970 --> 00:01:35,530
I should've been there.

18
00:01:39,040 --> 00:01:41,610
I should have been there with him.

19
00:02:30,860 --> 00:02:31,860
What's going on?

20
00:02:33,060 --> 00:02:34,060
No way.

21
00:02:34,990 --> 00:02:36,290
Am I dead?

22
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:43,900
Did I...

23
00:02:46,070 --> 00:02:47,940
really die?

24
00:02:51,180 --> 00:02:52,210
Mister.

25
00:02:55,310 --> 00:02:56,310
Who are you?

26
00:02:57,650 --> 00:02:58,650
Wait.

27
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:01,090
Who am I?

28
00:03:01,890 --> 00:03:02,990
Mister.

29
00:03:04,490 --> 00:03:05,860
You need to go that way.

30
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:09,560
That way?

31
00:03:10,460 --> 00:03:11,460
What's over there?

32
00:03:16,230 --> 00:03:17,840
- Mother! Over here! - What?

33
00:03:27,950 --> 00:03:28,950
Yi Rang.

34
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:33,050
Yi Rang, Mom's here.

35
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:36,850
Doctor, what's wrong with my boy? What's happening?

36
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:55,770
You can't go out there.

37
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:01,350
Mister, don't go.

38
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,880
What's wrong with my boy, Doctor?

39
00:04:07,050 --> 00:04:09,550
Please, save my boy, Doctor.

40
00:04:09,850 --> 00:04:13,460
- We've tried CPR several times. - Doctor.

41
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:15,030
Please, I'm begging you.

42
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:18,630
You promised...

43
00:04:20,770 --> 00:04:22,870
you'd find my mom for me.

44
00:04:32,410 --> 00:04:36,480
Patient Shin Yi Rang. Time of death, 8:43pm, August 16.

45
00:04:39,450 --> 00:04:41,790
- Doctor, look! - Charge the paddles!

46
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:44,990
- Hey! Look... - Family, please step this way.

47
00:04:45,860 --> 00:04:48,230
Please step outside for a moment. Quickly, this way.

48
00:04:48,730 --> 00:04:49,960
- This way... - Clear!

49
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:51,560
Shoot.

50
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:53,970
Charge to 200.

51
00:05:06,580 --> 00:05:07,850
We've got a rhythm.

52
00:05:14,350 --> 00:05:15,890
- Yi Rang. - Yi Rang.

53
00:05:15,950 --> 00:05:18,890
Can you see me? Yi Rang, are you with us?

54
00:05:25,960 --> 00:05:26,960
Yi Rang.

55
00:05:40,310 --> 00:05:47,250
(Phantom Lawyer)

56
00:05:47,350 --> 00:05:48,670
That was Reporter Park Sung Chan.

57
00:05:49,450 --> 00:05:53,560
We will bring you more updates on the Mr. Jo case as they come in.

58
00:05:53,860 --> 00:05:57,630
And now, let's meet the modern-day hero who saved young Kwon.

59
00:05:57,960 --> 00:05:59,830
- Reporter Kim Bo Ra, over to you. - It's on.

60
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:01,599
Thank you. I'm reporting live from the hospital...

61
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,920
where Shin Yi Rang is recovering.

62
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:05,399
Shin Yi Rang sustained a gunshot wound while rescuing Kwon,

63
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:06,599
but he is reportedly recovering well...

64
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:08,000
- after surgery. - He's coming out.

65
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:10,560
And we can see Shin Yi Rang coming out now.

66
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:14,810
- Mr. Shin, just a moment! - How are you feeling?

67
00:06:14,880 --> 00:06:16,380
- What motivated you? - Get the shot!

68
00:06:17,010 --> 00:06:19,080
- Please, just one comment! - How's your health?

69
00:06:19,150 --> 00:06:22,150
- How are you feeling? - Please, just one comment!

70
00:06:27,260 --> 00:06:29,490
Lightning...

71
00:06:30,190 --> 00:06:32,430
power.

72
00:06:33,970 --> 00:06:36,230
Power!

73
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:41,170
- Power! - Power!

74
00:06:41,940 --> 00:06:44,740
- Power! - Power!

75
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:47,910
Lightning...

76
00:06:49,410 --> 00:06:51,150
Power!

77
00:06:55,750 --> 00:06:57,590
Uncle.

78
00:06:57,990 --> 00:07:00,730
You were so awesome. The absolute best!

79
00:07:01,490 --> 00:07:03,460
- You did great. - I did?

80
00:07:04,230 --> 00:07:08,000
If my Da Bong says I'm awesome, then I must really be awesome.

81
00:07:08,570 --> 00:07:09,670
That's a relief.

82
00:07:11,470 --> 00:07:13,540
- Be careful. - Are you okay?

83
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:19,440
Get some rest, okay?

84
00:07:20,310 --> 00:07:22,310
- Thanks, everyone. - See you later.

85
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:24,450
Bong Soo Power!

86
00:07:25,350 --> 00:07:26,850
Yi Rang Power!

87
00:07:29,250 --> 00:07:30,450
- Here. - Goodness.

88
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:33,860
You've been through a lot. Just stay put. I'll be right back.

89
00:07:40,870 --> 00:07:42,070
Na Hyun cried?

90
00:07:42,530 --> 00:07:44,570
She said, "I should have been there with you."

91
00:07:45,170 --> 00:07:47,340
She said that and started crying her eyes out.

92
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:49,510
She did?

93
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:54,410
She was crying her eyes out?

94
00:08:00,420 --> 00:08:01,590
What are you so happy about?

95
00:08:02,820 --> 00:08:03,920
Na Hyun.

96
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:10,260
Are you okay? How can you be so reckless? Especially after getting shot.

97
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:13,130
I'm fine. Really.

98
00:08:17,940 --> 00:08:20,640
Mister, can I go to your place?

99
00:08:21,540 --> 00:08:25,840
Sure. It's boring here, so go home and play with Da Bong and Grandma.

100
00:08:26,540 --> 00:08:29,680
Okay! Yes!

101
00:08:33,950 --> 00:08:35,520
Si Ho's gone.

102
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:45,800
I scared you, didn't I?

103
00:08:47,430 --> 00:08:49,700
I was scared, and I was upset.

104
00:08:52,140 --> 00:08:55,070
You should've taken me or your brother-in-law with you.

105
00:08:55,670 --> 00:08:57,910
Why would you go somewhere so dangerous all by yourself?

106
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:59,110
You're right.

107
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:01,880
I guess I got ahead of myself.

108
00:09:02,980 --> 00:09:06,780
I was just so desperate to find out who Si Ho was.

109
00:09:10,090 --> 00:09:11,090
That reminds me.

110
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:14,290
The day you went looking for Si Ho,

111
00:09:14,860 --> 00:09:18,300
his father came by the office. He wanted to talk about getting a divorce.

112
00:09:19,030 --> 00:09:22,670
- A divorce? - They've been apart since Si Ho vanished.

113
00:09:23,370 --> 00:09:27,340
It seemed like they were both struggling with a lot of regret and guilt.

114
00:09:28,110 --> 00:09:31,680
Plus, not knowing if Si Ho is alive or not must be even more agonizing.

115
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:33,040
That's true.

116
00:09:34,610 --> 00:09:36,010
Sometimes a sliver of hope...

117
00:09:37,050 --> 00:09:38,580
can just be another form of torture.

118
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:44,660
So, what's the status of the investigation?

119
00:09:45,790 --> 00:09:49,690
Thanks to Ye Jun being rescued, we have Jo Chi Yeong in custody,

120
00:09:51,130 --> 00:09:54,400
but as for Si Ho, who went missing a year ago,

121
00:09:54,700 --> 00:09:56,200
Jo Chi Yeong is pleading the fifth.

122
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:59,300
Ye Jun and Si Ho are around the same age,

123
00:09:59,470 --> 00:10:03,010
and while it's true both kids were wearing yellow rain boots,

124
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:07,010
there's no hard evidence that Jo Chi Yeong kidnapped Si Ho.

125
00:10:10,980 --> 00:10:11,980
What are you doing?

126
00:10:12,820 --> 00:10:14,820
Kidnapping, false imprisonment of a child...

127
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:16,720
carries a sentence of ten years at most.

128
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:19,840
And in reality, he'll likely get a much lighter sentence.

129
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:21,880
How can I stand by and let that happen?

130
00:10:22,360 --> 00:10:24,030
(Seoin Hospital)

131
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:25,660
Here, put your arm around me like this.

132
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:28,900
Yi Rang got shot!

133
00:10:29,370 --> 00:10:30,400
Right. My bad, my bad.

134
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:34,569
Then let's at least walk in step. Like this. Left foot, left foot.

135
00:10:34,570 --> 00:10:36,740
Why are we marching? This isn't the army.

136
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:38,910
- Goodness. - Seriously!

137
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:41,610
Are you okay?

138
00:10:46,920 --> 00:10:50,290
I slept well. Now, it's time to make the bed.

139
00:10:50,520 --> 00:10:52,060
I want to play too.

140
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:55,730
- Honey, did you sleep well? - Of course.

141
00:10:57,360 --> 00:11:01,030
Now it's time for breakfast. After I eat...

142
00:11:01,730 --> 00:11:04,240
Honey, do you have a shoot today?

143
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:08,140
Yes. I'm playing a doctor today.

144
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:10,610
Oh my, that's so cool!

145
00:11:11,680 --> 00:11:14,180
Dad, can you please not go?

146
00:11:15,180 --> 00:11:16,880
I want to be with you.

147
00:11:17,450 --> 00:11:19,920
Should we take Da Bong to the theme park this weekend?

148
00:11:20,450 --> 00:11:23,690
Yes. That's a great idea. That's my girl.

149
00:11:24,460 --> 00:11:26,059
But I want to go camping.

150
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:29,530
- Have a great shoot. - Okay, I will.

151
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:43,140
Excuse me. I'm here about a boy named Yoon Si Ho.

152
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:47,450
Are you Si Ho's father?

153
00:11:49,250 --> 00:11:50,350
You know my Si Ho?

154
00:11:51,850 --> 00:11:53,350
I heard from the police.

155
00:11:54,220 --> 00:11:55,650
That he went missing one year ago.

156
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:02,190
I heard you saved a boy named Ye Jun.

157
00:12:03,690 --> 00:12:06,960
By any chance... Do you know...

158
00:12:08,070 --> 00:12:09,070
where my Si Ho is?

159
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,200
No.

160
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:14,440
I'm sorry.

161
00:12:17,740 --> 00:12:18,810
I see.

162
00:12:38,560 --> 00:12:39,560
Hey.

163
00:12:42,770 --> 00:12:43,770
He says he doesn't know.

164
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:48,770
Honey... Are you okay?

165
00:12:50,410 --> 00:12:51,690
Do you want me to come over now?

166
00:12:55,110 --> 00:12:57,080
Okay, sorry. I was just...

167
00:12:58,850 --> 00:13:00,520
Our Si Ho will be okay.

168
00:13:01,150 --> 00:13:02,430
Let's just wait a little longer.

169
00:13:03,490 --> 00:13:04,490
Okay?

170
00:13:11,100 --> 00:13:13,700
He said he'd let you ride in his police car?

171
00:13:15,230 --> 00:13:16,230
Yes.

172
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,740
But he was a total stranger.

173
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:20,440
Weren't you scared?

174
00:13:20,870 --> 00:13:22,370
But I had seen him before.

175
00:13:23,170 --> 00:13:27,380
That police officer came to my school to teach a safety class.

176
00:13:29,680 --> 00:13:32,550
That would've made him easier to trust.

177
00:13:33,050 --> 00:13:35,820
And he was really nice to me.

178
00:13:36,850 --> 00:13:39,890
He even showed me his gun and played with me.

179
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:43,360
But...

180
00:13:44,160 --> 00:13:46,530
When it got dark, I told him I wanted to go home.

181
00:13:47,730 --> 00:13:49,730
He said we were going somewhere fun tomorrow...

182
00:13:50,030 --> 00:13:51,370
so I should just wait.

183
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:57,010
But I insisted on going home,

184
00:13:57,110 --> 00:13:58,580
and he got really mad.

185
00:14:00,710 --> 00:14:01,910
Actually...

186
00:14:02,810 --> 00:14:05,380
my head had been hurting since that morning,

187
00:14:07,620 --> 00:14:09,390
but when he started yelling,

188
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:11,790
my head started to hurt even more.

189
00:14:13,690 --> 00:14:14,690
Si Ho...

190
00:14:15,360 --> 00:14:16,400
Were you in a lot of pain?

191
00:14:17,930 --> 00:14:18,930
Yes.

192
00:14:20,730 --> 00:14:21,830
So...

193
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:25,220
I took some medicine and fell asleep for a long time.

194
00:14:25,870 --> 00:14:27,300
And when I opened my eyes,

195
00:14:28,070 --> 00:14:29,870
I was in your office.

196
00:14:33,380 --> 00:14:34,380
I see.

197
00:14:39,620 --> 00:14:41,890
I miss my mom and dad.

198
00:14:43,450 --> 00:14:44,860
Can't I go see them?

199
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:51,460
Si Ho.

200
00:14:52,560 --> 00:14:53,800
It might be hard...

201
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:57,670
to see your mom and dad right now.

202
00:14:58,800 --> 00:14:59,870
Why?

203
00:15:01,370 --> 00:15:02,570
Because your mom and dad...

204
00:15:04,710 --> 00:15:06,510
are a little sick.

205
00:15:07,580 --> 00:15:10,210
Really? What's wrong with them?

206
00:15:11,620 --> 00:15:13,150
Their hearts are sick.

207
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:15,720
Why?

208
00:15:17,660 --> 00:15:18,760
Let's say...

209
00:15:20,120 --> 00:15:22,960
one of your friends fell down right next to you?

210
00:15:23,530 --> 00:15:25,530
How do you think you would feel?

211
00:15:29,570 --> 00:15:30,730
I'd feel bad.

212
00:15:32,170 --> 00:15:33,740
Because I couldn't catch them.

213
00:15:34,910 --> 00:15:35,910
Exactly.

214
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:39,510
You know that feeling when you're sorry,

215
00:15:40,010 --> 00:15:41,490
even when it's not your fault, right?

216
00:15:42,510 --> 00:15:44,850
I think that's what your mom and dad are feeling.

217
00:15:48,650 --> 00:15:50,550
You're so precious to them,

218
00:15:51,890 --> 00:15:53,790
and they feel they couldn't protect you.

219
00:15:55,730 --> 00:15:59,400
They think, "What if I'd done this?" or "What if I'd done that?"

220
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:02,800
And they keep blaming themselves.

221
00:16:05,570 --> 00:16:06,570
That's why...

222
00:16:07,640 --> 00:16:09,710
it's making their hearts hurt even more.

223
00:16:10,810 --> 00:16:12,340
But they shouldn't feel that way.

224
00:16:14,310 --> 00:16:17,410
How does a hurting heart get better?

225
00:16:18,450 --> 00:16:22,420
I just want Mom and Dad to be happy again.

226
00:16:26,790 --> 00:16:30,260
If they knew you were doing so well,

227
00:16:31,130 --> 00:16:32,890
don't you think they'd start to feel better?

228
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:37,770
But Mom and Dad don't know that.

229
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:41,210
They can't see me...

230
00:16:42,010 --> 00:16:43,540
or hear from me.

231
00:16:44,210 --> 00:16:47,110
Don't worry. I'll help you.

232
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:50,480
Okay.

233
00:16:52,220 --> 00:16:53,320
All right then.

234
00:16:53,850 --> 00:16:54,950
High-five.

235
00:17:16,810 --> 00:17:19,080
Let's go. I'll take the bag.

236
00:17:23,150 --> 00:17:27,749
- Just a second. Sorry. - Seriously, stop it.

237
00:17:27,750 --> 00:17:28,990
Okay, fine.

238
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:38,360
You're here early.

239
00:17:39,160 --> 00:17:41,870
- How are you feeling? - I'm fine. Let's get started.

240
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:47,339
Jo Chi Yeong left his wife for an affair...

241
00:17:47,340 --> 00:17:48,910
and was raising their son, Gyeong Seo.

242
00:17:49,210 --> 00:17:51,680
Two years ago, while he was in the bathroom,

243
00:17:51,780 --> 00:17:53,480
Gyeong Seo climbed onto a desk...

244
00:17:53,580 --> 00:17:55,710
and fell to his death after the window screen ripped.

245
00:17:57,080 --> 00:18:00,620
Following the incident, his ex-wife accused him of child neglect,

246
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:03,719
but the court ruled that, as a busy cop,

247
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:05,890
he had not been a negligent father.

248
00:18:06,520 --> 00:18:10,360
From what I hear, there doesn't seem to be anything out of the ordinary.

249
00:18:11,330 --> 00:18:13,160
So a man who lost his child in an accident...

250
00:18:13,630 --> 00:18:16,470
goes on to kidnap and murder other children?

251
00:18:20,870 --> 00:18:22,110
So we're back to square one.

252
00:18:23,470 --> 00:18:25,510
What evidence do we have?

253
00:18:26,280 --> 00:18:30,180
These are the crime scene photos from when Jo Chi Yeong's son fell.

254
00:18:30,280 --> 00:18:31,850
(Crime scene photos)

255
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:33,220
(Eat pizza! Get a prize!)

256
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:38,460
Gosh. He must have really liked pizza.

257
00:18:38,760 --> 00:18:41,760
He collected a lot of coupons. He even drew his own.

258
00:18:42,060 --> 00:18:46,200
If he was drawing fake coupons, it might not have been about the pizza.

259
00:18:46,300 --> 00:18:48,340
He could have been trying to win one of the prizes.

260
00:18:48,570 --> 00:18:50,100
What were the prizes?

261
00:18:50,970 --> 00:18:52,640
- That's it. - What?

262
00:18:54,270 --> 00:18:56,540
Are you saying a six-year-old...

263
00:18:56,940 --> 00:18:58,660
was collecting coupons for a kimchi fridge?

264
00:18:59,280 --> 00:19:01,950
No way. Hold on, let me see... When was that?

265
00:19:02,080 --> 00:19:04,979
About three years ago, a local supermarket had a grand opening,

266
00:19:04,980 --> 00:19:06,820
and they had one of those big prize giveaways.

267
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:11,660
My daughter, Da Bong, won the grand prize, a TV.

268
00:19:12,190 --> 00:19:14,630
But my Da Bong started crying.

269
00:19:15,330 --> 00:19:17,960
- Why? - What she really wanted...

270
00:19:18,460 --> 00:19:20,380
was the fifth-place prize, a character backpack.

271
00:19:21,530 --> 00:19:24,740
What adults and kids value are completely different.

272
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:29,239
So if we look at this through a child's eyes...

273
00:19:29,240 --> 00:19:30,540
(Trip to a camp ground)

274
00:19:31,810 --> 00:19:32,910
What about this one?

275
00:19:34,110 --> 00:19:37,580
That makes sense. Kids love camping.

276
00:19:39,520 --> 00:19:41,120
I want to go camping.

277
00:19:41,950 --> 00:19:44,020
He told me we were going somewhere fun tomorrow,

278
00:19:44,290 --> 00:19:45,690
so he told me to just wait.

279
00:19:46,190 --> 00:19:49,560
Jo Chi Yeong told Si Ho they were going somewhere fun the next day.

280
00:19:49,790 --> 00:19:51,830
That could be the camp ground.

281
00:19:52,530 --> 00:19:56,170
Si Ho also said Jo Chi Yeong came to his school for a safety lesson.

282
00:19:56,600 --> 00:19:58,400
What if that's when Jo Chi Yeong...

283
00:19:58,840 --> 00:20:01,610
was looking for a potential target...

284
00:20:02,170 --> 00:20:05,180
and was trying to give himself another chance?

285
00:20:07,180 --> 00:20:09,310
For the man who couldn't protect his own son?

286
00:20:09,710 --> 00:20:13,180
In fact, Jo Chi Yeong called Ye Jun his son.

287
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:16,090
And he fed Ye Jun the same kind of pizza his own son loved.

288
00:20:16,420 --> 00:20:19,520
So you're saying he wasn't looking for someone to get revenge on,

289
00:20:19,590 --> 00:20:22,730
but trying to give himself a chance to be a good father?

290
00:20:23,060 --> 00:20:27,300
- That's completely insane. - If he planned to take Si Ho...

291
00:20:27,630 --> 00:20:29,470
to the camp ground his own son wanted to go to,

292
00:20:29,830 --> 00:20:32,670
it's possible he buried Si Ho there.

293
00:20:33,040 --> 00:20:36,240
- It's possible, but that's a reach. - It's a long shot, I know.

294
00:20:36,770 --> 00:20:39,130
That's why I'm going to meet with Jo Chi Yeong and ask him.

295
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:43,210
- Do you think he'll agree to see you? - Even if he won't see me,

296
00:20:44,620 --> 00:20:46,920
he'll want to see Si Ho.

297
00:20:56,790 --> 00:20:59,899
(Jo Chi Yeong)

298
00:20:59,900 --> 00:21:03,500
(Sender: 2nd Floor, Pit-a-Pat Butcher Restaurant)

299
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:21,690
Dear Officer.

300
00:21:22,620 --> 00:21:25,060
Mister, it's me, Si Ho.

301
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:28,730
It's Yoon Si Ho. You said you liked the back of my head.

302
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:33,760
We played a word chain game and cops and robbers,

303
00:21:34,630 --> 00:21:38,800
and you even showed me your gun. You remember, right?

304
00:21:41,440 --> 00:21:43,910
If Jo Chi Yeong won't talk,

305
00:21:44,010 --> 00:21:46,010
I need you and Bong Soo to go to the camp ground...

306
00:21:46,180 --> 00:21:47,380
and search for Si Ho.

307
00:21:47,780 --> 00:21:48,850
Got it.

308
00:21:55,950 --> 00:22:01,590
(Good Sleeping Camp ground)

309
00:22:03,760 --> 00:22:07,760
This is it? Just one officer?

310
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:10,430
I had to come in on my day off.

311
00:22:10,770 --> 00:22:12,810
That's because we still don't have enough evidence.

312
00:22:13,540 --> 00:22:17,210
Still, a hero of our time is saying it. They should trust him.

313
00:22:17,410 --> 00:22:18,510
Tell me about it.

314
00:22:20,680 --> 00:22:22,800
How are we supposed to find him in a place this huge?

315
00:22:23,380 --> 00:22:24,380
We have to.

316
00:22:25,150 --> 00:22:28,550
With the Lord, nothing is impossible. There may only be four of us,

317
00:22:29,020 --> 00:22:32,360
but he will give us the strength of 40, or even 400 men.

318
00:22:32,920 --> 00:22:33,920
Amen.

319
00:22:34,990 --> 00:22:35,990
Amen.

320
00:22:37,090 --> 00:22:39,430
All right, let me give you the rundown.

321
00:22:40,030 --> 00:22:42,129
Plant growth is different where a body is buried...

322
00:22:42,130 --> 00:22:43,530
due to the organic matter.

323
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:45,399
So, keep an eye out for places where...

324
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:47,270
plants look different or are discoloured.

325
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:50,770
Also, I've just sent a metal detector app to your phones.

326
00:22:50,970 --> 00:22:52,539
Run it and hold it to the ground.

327
00:22:52,540 --> 00:22:56,350
Things like buttons, keys, or zippers will set it off right away.

328
00:22:58,820 --> 00:23:00,950
Lawyer Han and Father,

329
00:23:01,690 --> 00:23:03,449
you two take that area.

330
00:23:03,450 --> 00:23:05,860
The officer and I will take this side. Okay?

331
00:23:05,960 --> 00:23:06,960
Right.

332
00:23:07,790 --> 00:23:09,510
But are you a police officer by any chance?

333
00:23:16,500 --> 00:23:17,600
Let's get going.

334
00:23:19,040 --> 00:23:20,240
I'll do my best.

335
00:23:37,220 --> 00:23:38,290
You again.

336
00:23:40,860 --> 00:23:41,990
Who are you?

337
00:23:46,100 --> 00:23:47,360
Who do you think you are,

338
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:49,830
sending me something like that?

339
00:23:55,870 --> 00:23:57,070
Si Ho is...

340
00:23:59,280 --> 00:24:00,380
right here with me.

341
00:24:04,280 --> 00:24:07,380
- What are you talking about? - Then how else would I know...

342
00:24:08,020 --> 00:24:09,260
things only you and Si Ho knew?

343
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:13,160
Stop lying.

344
00:24:14,890 --> 00:24:18,530
- I said, stop messing with me. - You kidnapped Ye Jun and Si Ho...

345
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:21,830
and caused Si Ho's death.

346
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:26,040
To anyone else, you're a shameless and heinous criminal.

347
00:24:26,570 --> 00:24:27,570
But I...

348
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:32,520
believe that Jo Chi Yeong, Gyeong Seo's father,

349
00:24:34,280 --> 00:24:35,880
might be a little different.

350
00:24:45,920 --> 00:24:47,290
I'm begging you.

351
00:24:48,120 --> 00:24:49,330
Gyeong Seo's father.

352
00:24:50,190 --> 00:24:52,200
Please, think of Si Ho's parents.

353
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:55,100
They can't even find their beloved son's body,

354
00:24:56,530 --> 00:24:58,810
and they've been barely living with that pain ever since.

355
00:25:01,440 --> 00:25:03,316
You've lost a child yourself, so you know how that feels.

356
00:25:03,340 --> 00:25:04,540
Don't you dare run your mouth.

357
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:08,310
You wanted to forgive yourself, didn't you?

358
00:25:09,450 --> 00:25:10,850
After Gyeong Seo died,

359
00:25:12,320 --> 00:25:13,980
you must have been filled with regrets.

360
00:25:15,490 --> 00:25:18,920
So by doing for those other kids what you couldn't do for Gyeong Seo,

361
00:25:19,520 --> 00:25:21,766
you were telling yourself that you weren't a bad father...

362
00:25:21,790 --> 00:25:23,829
- to make yourself feel better. - Shut up, you son of a gun!

363
00:25:23,830 --> 00:25:25,550
All for such a pathetic, ridiculous reason,

364
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:29,100
you traumatized Ye Jun for life and caused Si Ho's death.

365
00:25:30,530 --> 00:25:33,370
- You've crushed his parents' hearts. - What do you know?

366
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:37,640
Oh, I know.

367
00:25:40,310 --> 00:25:41,710
To a child, their parents...

368
00:25:43,680 --> 00:25:44,950
are their entire world.

369
00:25:50,490 --> 00:25:53,390
You took away the most precious thing they had.

370
00:26:12,880 --> 00:26:14,410
I don't know who Si Ho is.

371
00:26:16,410 --> 00:26:20,220
Besides, if his parents truly loved him,

372
00:26:22,690 --> 00:26:24,350
they wouldn't have left him all alone.

373
00:26:26,090 --> 00:26:27,420
Parents like that...

374
00:26:29,130 --> 00:26:30,590
don't deserve to be parents.

375
00:26:38,100 --> 00:26:40,570
Don't say that about my mom and dad.

376
00:26:42,610 --> 00:26:46,540
My mom and dad... They loved me.

377
00:26:47,440 --> 00:26:49,250
They did everything for me.

378
00:26:50,880 --> 00:26:52,820
To buy me yummy food,

379
00:26:53,620 --> 00:26:55,590
my mom wouldn't buy makeup for herself.

380
00:26:56,620 --> 00:26:59,520
And my dad worked late into the night...

381
00:27:00,190 --> 00:27:02,130
just to buy me pretty rain boots.

382
00:27:03,560 --> 00:27:07,260
They're my one and only mom and dad.

383
00:27:08,570 --> 00:27:10,800
And I love them so, so much.

384
00:27:12,070 --> 00:27:15,770
I wouldn't trade them for a hundred pizzas,

385
00:27:16,210 --> 00:27:20,780
or for the whole amusement park. I would never trade my mom and dad.

386
00:27:26,320 --> 00:27:27,950
Mister...

387
00:27:29,490 --> 00:27:31,250
Why are you trying to replace them?

388
00:27:35,190 --> 00:27:37,490
I'm not your son.

389
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:45,340
He must have loved you so, so much too.

390
00:27:49,640 --> 00:27:52,040
If I were your son,

391
00:27:53,080 --> 00:27:54,840
I think I'd be heartbroken.

392
00:28:00,620 --> 00:28:01,950
Mister.

393
00:28:03,490 --> 00:28:04,920
Why are you crying?

394
00:28:07,790 --> 00:28:08,790
I...

395
00:28:11,260 --> 00:28:13,460
I wanted to be a good dad to Gyeong Seo.

396
00:28:16,430 --> 00:28:18,470
I felt like it was my fault he didn't have a mom,

397
00:28:20,540 --> 00:28:22,640
and that I was wrong for leaving him alone.

398
00:28:27,210 --> 00:28:28,410
If I could just do it over,

399
00:28:29,810 --> 00:28:32,320
I thought I could finally do it right.

400
00:28:42,960 --> 00:28:44,830
I didn't even know you were that sick.

401
00:28:46,200 --> 00:28:47,900
I just thought you had a fever.

402
00:28:49,170 --> 00:28:51,290
When I came back in the morning and found you dead...

403
00:28:52,340 --> 00:28:54,000
You have no idea how shocked I was.

404
00:28:58,510 --> 00:28:59,610
I'm sorry...

405
00:29:02,350 --> 00:29:04,180
I really am so sorry.

406
00:29:07,550 --> 00:29:09,690
If you're really sorry,

407
00:29:11,350 --> 00:29:13,690
then please take me to my mom and dad.

408
00:29:16,790 --> 00:29:19,730
Where am I right now?

409
00:29:37,010 --> 00:29:39,180
Move. To the right. Your right.

410
00:29:53,030 --> 00:29:54,130
What?

411
00:30:06,210 --> 00:30:07,680
Si Ho...

412
00:30:15,420 --> 00:30:16,520
Do you think it'll be okay?

413
00:30:18,790 --> 00:30:21,760
They said they're both ready now.

414
00:30:24,060 --> 00:30:25,600
And Si Ho will be okay, right?

415
00:30:26,630 --> 00:30:29,070
He's going to see how awkward things are between his parents.

416
00:30:29,930 --> 00:30:32,600
Still, they're his mom and dad.

417
00:30:56,290 --> 00:30:58,290
All right. Shall we go?

418
00:30:59,430 --> 00:31:00,530
Yes.

419
00:32:03,490 --> 00:32:04,690
(Rice Crackers)

420
00:32:13,840 --> 00:32:14,840
Si Ho.

421
00:32:16,810 --> 00:32:18,340
I was too late, wasn't I?

422
00:32:21,510 --> 00:32:22,510
I'm sorry.

423
00:32:26,950 --> 00:32:28,950
(Run! Kitty Kindergarten)

424
00:32:33,560 --> 00:32:35,220
My sweet Si Ho, have you been okay?

425
00:32:41,330 --> 00:32:42,430
Si Ho.

426
00:32:44,130 --> 00:32:45,370
Mommy's here.

427
00:32:46,670 --> 00:32:47,830
You missed Mommy, didn't you?

428
00:32:50,610 --> 00:32:53,540
Look at this. Look at all these flowers.

429
00:32:55,380 --> 00:32:57,260
It looks like a lot of your friends stopped by.

430
00:32:59,080 --> 00:33:00,080
Si Ho...

431
00:33:28,440 --> 00:33:29,750
Mommy!

432
00:33:30,650 --> 00:33:32,480
- Daddy! - Si Ho!

433
00:33:32,680 --> 00:33:33,720
Si Ho!

434
00:33:34,680 --> 00:33:35,890
Si Ho, come here.

435
00:33:41,460 --> 00:33:43,960
My sweet Si Ho, there you are.

436
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:51,470
Wasn't that jump a little low?

437
00:34:04,380 --> 00:34:05,920
I have to go now, don't I?

438
00:34:10,750 --> 00:34:12,190
How did you know?

439
00:34:12,590 --> 00:34:15,530
Because you look so sad.

440
00:34:18,390 --> 00:34:19,600
But please,

441
00:34:20,530 --> 00:34:22,000
don't be sad.

442
00:34:23,500 --> 00:34:27,300
I'm so happy I got to see my mom and dad getting along before I go.

443
00:34:28,940 --> 00:34:29,970
So...

444
00:34:30,940 --> 00:34:32,240
you should smile.

445
00:34:37,510 --> 00:34:39,180
Thank you so much for everything.

446
00:34:39,850 --> 00:34:44,820
You're way cooler than Lightning Man. A hundred, a thousand times cooler.

447
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:50,360
Me?

448
00:34:52,160 --> 00:34:54,860
What's so cool about me?

449
00:34:55,530 --> 00:34:56,630
You're kind,

450
00:34:57,600 --> 00:34:58,940
handsome,

451
00:35:02,610 --> 00:35:03,870
and you're super weak.

452
00:35:04,310 --> 00:35:06,980
Seriously... What kind of compliment is that?

453
00:35:07,380 --> 00:35:11,450
It's really hard for a weak person to save someone else.

454
00:35:14,120 --> 00:35:18,090
So I managed to do something that difficult?

455
00:35:18,450 --> 00:35:21,060
Yes, you're so cool.

456
00:35:21,360 --> 00:35:25,360
I bet your dad is really proud of you in the skies.

457
00:35:30,530 --> 00:35:32,640
Thanks, Lightning Man.

458
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:36,510
You were pretty cool yourself.

459
00:35:40,380 --> 00:35:41,880
Si Ho, I...

460
00:35:42,610 --> 00:35:44,780
have one last gift for you.

461
00:35:45,110 --> 00:35:46,120
You do?

462
00:35:46,750 --> 00:35:49,450
One, two,

463
00:35:50,190 --> 00:35:51,190
three!

464
00:35:54,390 --> 00:35:57,830
Lightning Power!

465
00:36:02,130 --> 00:36:05,230
Lightning Power!

466
00:36:07,440 --> 00:36:11,039
- Lightning Power! - Power!

467
00:36:11,040 --> 00:36:12,110
Power!

468
00:36:16,710 --> 00:36:18,010
Goodbye, Si Ho.

469
00:36:19,850 --> 00:36:20,950
Bye.

470
00:36:54,920 --> 00:36:58,820
Yi Rang, I'm so glad you got out so quickly.

471
00:36:58,890 --> 00:37:02,020
- Yi Rang is in great shape. - Tell me about it.

472
00:37:02,260 --> 00:37:04,760
- Thanks for the food. - Go on, eat plenty.

473
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:08,730
All right, how about a toast to Yi Rang's health?

474
00:37:09,500 --> 00:37:10,900
Cheers!

475
00:37:11,430 --> 00:37:14,640
- Right. Da Bong should join in too. - Cheers!

476
00:37:28,320 --> 00:37:29,320
What?

477
00:37:29,321 --> 00:37:30,761
I said you should eat something too.

478
00:37:34,190 --> 00:37:35,190
Okay.

479
00:37:35,860 --> 00:37:37,940
Don't just grill the meat. You have to eat some too.

480
00:37:45,030 --> 00:37:47,600
Why are you only giving food to Yi Rang?

481
00:37:49,240 --> 00:37:50,340
Well...

482
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:54,680
Yi Rang is my only colleague, so I have to look out for him.

483
00:37:54,840 --> 00:37:59,280
Hey, now I'm starting to feel left out. I worked really hard to help too.

484
00:37:59,320 --> 00:38:01,220
You did more than just help.

485
00:38:01,750 --> 00:38:06,660
You're an indispensable part of the firm, a true asset.

486
00:38:06,920 --> 00:38:09,460
Like our general manager?

487
00:38:10,190 --> 00:38:11,990
- Oh, my. - Right?

488
00:38:12,800 --> 00:38:14,700
Yes. The general manager.

489
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:17,570
Wait, you're not just saying that? A real general manager?

490
00:38:17,700 --> 00:38:21,470
Of course! Here you go, General Manager. Let me fill your glass.

491
00:38:23,270 --> 00:38:27,410
- Goodness. - To our very first General Manager...

492
00:38:27,580 --> 00:38:30,610
of Shin Yi Rang Law Office.

493
00:38:30,680 --> 00:38:32,820
- Cheers! - Cheers!

494
00:38:33,050 --> 00:38:34,750
Daddy's the new General Manager.

495
00:38:41,660 --> 00:38:42,760
Eat up.

496
00:38:45,060 --> 00:38:48,230
(Chairman Yang Byung Il)

497
00:38:48,300 --> 00:38:50,276
(Attorney Shin Yi Rang, key to the search for Yoon Si Ho's body...)

498
00:38:50,300 --> 00:38:52,300
(Represents victim's family in civil suit)

499
00:38:56,410 --> 00:39:00,440
(Chairman Yang Byung Il)

500
00:39:00,510 --> 00:39:03,280
(He played a major role in the search for Yoon Si Ho's body.)

501
00:39:03,350 --> 00:39:05,830
(Shin Yi Rang has been confirmed to be a practising attorney.)

502
00:39:10,620 --> 00:39:12,249
(Statement of claim for damages for torts...)

503
00:39:12,250 --> 00:39:13,850
(in the Yoon Si Ho abuse and death case)

504
00:39:22,630 --> 00:39:26,140
(Taebaek)

505
00:39:29,610 --> 00:39:31,310
I told you. I have to go see Shin Yi Rang.

506
00:39:35,510 --> 00:39:36,510
Yes?

507
00:39:41,620 --> 00:39:42,820
Sir, you have some mail.

508
00:39:45,960 --> 00:39:50,460
- What's that one? - International mail for the Chairman.

509
00:39:52,290 --> 00:39:53,690
Give it to me. I'll take it to him.

510
00:39:53,930 --> 00:39:54,930
Okay.

511
00:39:59,140 --> 00:40:00,840
(Davith Medical Center)

512
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:03,400
This is from the hospital where father had his surgery.

513
00:40:13,080 --> 00:40:14,320
(To Mr. Yang Byung Il)

514
00:40:21,790 --> 00:40:24,590
(You voluntarily stopped the treatment our medical staff recommended.)

515
00:40:24,690 --> 00:40:26,629
(And as a result, any medical consequences that may arise...)

516
00:40:26,630 --> 00:40:27,930
(are your sole responsibility.)

517
00:40:35,470 --> 00:40:37,970
- I should get going. - Drive safe.

518
00:40:38,210 --> 00:40:39,310
Come visit again soon.

519
00:40:39,710 --> 00:40:43,050
Ms. Pretty. Get home safe.

520
00:40:44,910 --> 00:40:46,020
General Manager.

521
00:40:48,020 --> 00:40:50,250
I'm going to walk Na Hyun out.

522
00:40:50,620 --> 00:40:51,890
Don't bother coming back.

523
00:40:52,590 --> 00:40:53,990
Bye.

524
00:40:57,560 --> 00:40:59,330
I'm in such a great mood.

525
00:40:59,830 --> 00:41:00,930
I'm feeling good.

526
00:41:01,930 --> 00:41:03,130
Our General Manager.

527
00:41:03,800 --> 00:41:04,900
That's right!

528
00:41:10,170 --> 00:41:11,810
Wasn't there something you wanted to say?

529
00:41:12,780 --> 00:41:15,410
About what?

530
00:41:16,810 --> 00:41:19,920
Back at Sky Park, and at the hospital too.

531
00:41:21,150 --> 00:41:23,070
You started to say something but never finished.

532
00:41:32,830 --> 00:41:33,830
What are you doing?

533
00:41:36,030 --> 00:41:37,790
It's just that at all the important moments,

534
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:40,570
a ghost seems to interrupt, so I was telling you to be careful.

535
00:41:43,240 --> 00:41:44,340
Then tomorrow...

536
00:41:45,140 --> 00:41:47,340
why don't we meet somewhere even a ghost can't find us?

537
00:41:48,680 --> 00:41:50,210
We can get a good meal...

538
00:41:50,850 --> 00:41:52,410
and say what we've been meaning to say.

539
00:41:54,050 --> 00:41:56,450
You have something to tell me too?

540
00:41:57,420 --> 00:41:58,420
Of course I do.

541
00:42:01,890 --> 00:42:04,730
I'm not in trouble, am I?

542
00:42:05,030 --> 00:42:06,500
No, of course not.

543
00:42:07,160 --> 00:42:09,270
Or maybe you are.

544
00:42:10,570 --> 00:42:11,670
I am?

545
00:42:12,740 --> 00:42:14,600
What did I do this time?

546
00:42:17,940 --> 00:42:21,580
Come on, Na Hyun. It's better to just rip the band-aid off.

547
00:42:21,640 --> 00:42:23,280
Can't you just tell me now?

548
00:42:23,810 --> 00:42:24,810
No.

549
00:42:25,680 --> 00:42:27,180
Why not? Please, just tell me.

550
00:42:28,950 --> 00:42:29,950
Goodness.

551
00:42:41,430 --> 00:42:43,800
This is way too late, but happy birthday.

552
00:42:44,430 --> 00:42:47,370
I know I missed the day, but I really wanted to give this to you.

553
00:42:54,710 --> 00:42:56,630
I can't believe I'm only giving this to you now.

554
00:43:21,440 --> 00:43:22,740
Attorney Shin Yi Rang?

555
00:43:23,240 --> 00:43:26,740
Yes. Attorney Han?

556
00:43:28,480 --> 00:43:29,960
Sounds like you're out of the office.

557
00:43:30,510 --> 00:43:34,250
Yes. I'm getting the retainer agreement signed by Mr. Yoon Jae Uk.

558
00:43:35,680 --> 00:43:37,820
What are you up to, Attorney Han?

559
00:43:38,450 --> 00:43:40,490
CEO Kang Ji Hoon from Ideal Shoes...

560
00:43:40,590 --> 00:43:42,360
asked me to look over a contract for him.

561
00:43:42,930 --> 00:43:45,090
He's signing a new deal with an online platform.

562
00:43:46,530 --> 00:43:47,530
That's great.

563
00:43:50,930 --> 00:43:52,530
We're still on for later, right?

564
00:43:53,570 --> 00:43:54,940
I texted you the location.

565
00:43:55,570 --> 00:43:57,110
Yes, I got it.

566
00:43:58,270 --> 00:44:00,680
Okay, I'll be there by eight.

567
00:44:01,440 --> 00:44:03,410
Okay, see you later.

568
00:44:24,530 --> 00:44:25,930
You seem to be in a good mood.

569
00:44:30,370 --> 00:44:32,040
(Yoon Si Ho)

570
00:44:34,510 --> 00:44:36,650
Oh, boy. Looks like the lawyer's here.

571
00:44:43,520 --> 00:44:45,349
(Yang Do Kyung)

572
00:44:45,350 --> 00:44:46,560
Yes?

573
00:44:49,260 --> 00:44:50,260
Are you busy?

574
00:44:51,060 --> 00:44:53,730
- No, Dad. - If you haven't eaten, let's eat.

575
00:45:23,690 --> 00:45:26,930
The call could not be connected. Please leave a message after the tone...

576
00:45:27,300 --> 00:45:28,400
That's weird.

577
00:45:29,430 --> 00:45:30,570
Where could he be?

578
00:45:35,840 --> 00:45:36,840
Huh?

579
00:45:37,670 --> 00:45:40,880
You're here. I was worried when you didn't pick up.

580
00:45:41,040 --> 00:45:42,480
I'm dropping the case.

581
00:45:43,780 --> 00:45:44,780
Please leave.

582
00:45:46,050 --> 00:45:47,920
- What? - Because I don't want to talk to you.

583
00:45:49,520 --> 00:45:50,520
I said, leave.

584
00:45:51,250 --> 00:45:52,250
Sir...

585
00:45:53,060 --> 00:45:56,330
Mr. Yoon, what happened?

586
00:45:57,890 --> 00:45:59,960
I'm truly grateful that you found my Si Ho,

587
00:46:02,230 --> 00:46:04,310
and I know very well that you've done nothing wrong.

588
00:46:05,970 --> 00:46:08,940
But when I think about your father, I just can't stand it.

589
00:46:09,840 --> 00:46:11,410
Because of Shin Gi Jung, my father...

590
00:46:14,910 --> 00:46:15,980
Please, just go.

591
00:46:23,690 --> 00:46:26,620
It's been a while since we've had a meal like this, just the two of us.

592
00:46:28,320 --> 00:46:32,130
You're right. When I was healthy, I was busy with work,

593
00:46:32,760 --> 00:46:34,100
and when I finally had free time,

594
00:46:34,900 --> 00:46:36,600
I was away from home because I was sick.

595
00:46:38,230 --> 00:46:39,600
Now that you're healthy again,

596
00:46:40,440 --> 00:46:41,760
so let's do this more often, Dad.

597
00:46:42,200 --> 00:46:43,210
Okay.

598
00:46:47,810 --> 00:46:48,840
Does that mean...

599
00:46:49,040 --> 00:46:51,480
you don't have to go back to the hospital in America anymore?

600
00:46:51,710 --> 00:46:54,070
The treatment is finished, so there's no reason to go back.

601
00:46:55,680 --> 00:46:56,690
Right.

602
00:46:58,690 --> 00:47:00,220
Being sick taught me something.

603
00:47:01,490 --> 00:47:02,860
What's most important in life.

604
00:47:03,990 --> 00:47:07,360
Money, fame, status... They're all meaningless.

605
00:47:09,100 --> 00:47:10,820
In the end, the only thing you have left...

606
00:47:11,800 --> 00:47:12,800
is family.

607
00:47:15,240 --> 00:47:16,410
Your grandfather...

608
00:47:18,370 --> 00:47:20,480
never gave me a single compliment.

609
00:47:22,010 --> 00:47:24,580
He'd always ask, "Is that the best you can do?"

610
00:47:25,880 --> 00:47:26,920
And I would always...

611
00:47:27,920 --> 00:47:29,790
answer that I would work harder.

612
00:47:31,520 --> 00:47:32,720
Since that's how I was raised,

613
00:47:33,360 --> 00:47:35,520
I wasn't able to be very affectionate with you either.

614
00:47:38,660 --> 00:47:40,260
But one thing I can say for certain...

615
00:47:41,530 --> 00:47:44,100
is that no matter what, I will protect you.

616
00:47:45,500 --> 00:47:46,780
Because that's what family does.

617
00:47:48,000 --> 00:47:49,540
And I trust you'll do the same.

618
00:47:53,910 --> 00:47:56,650
You trust me?

619
00:47:57,010 --> 00:47:58,050
Yes.

620
00:47:58,910 --> 00:47:59,980
I trust my son.

621
00:48:05,020 --> 00:48:06,420
Don't you worry about a thing, Dad.

622
00:48:07,660 --> 00:48:08,820
I'll protect you.

623
00:48:12,490 --> 00:48:14,860
All right. Let's eat.

624
00:48:37,350 --> 00:48:42,090
(Shin Yi Rang Law Office, Pit-a-Pat Butcher Restaurant)

625
00:48:44,530 --> 00:48:47,400
But when I think about your father, I just can't stand it.

626
00:48:48,700 --> 00:48:50,300
Because of Shin Gi Jung, my father...

627
00:49:00,180 --> 00:49:03,280
(Pit-a-Pat Butcher Restaurant)

628
00:49:05,150 --> 00:49:06,880
(Prosecutor Kim Hyun Woo)

629
00:49:12,920 --> 00:49:13,920
Yes, Prosecutor?

630
00:49:13,990 --> 00:49:17,859
Lawyer Shin. I'm calling about the Yoon Jae Uk case.

631
00:49:17,860 --> 00:49:19,160
Is now a good time to talk?

632
00:49:20,360 --> 00:49:23,870
Actually, I don't think I can take that case.

633
00:49:25,800 --> 00:49:29,170
Mr. Yoon Jae Uk has cancelled his retainer.

634
00:49:30,540 --> 00:49:32,070
What? Why is that?

635
00:49:32,570 --> 00:49:35,380
I'm not entirely sure.

636
00:49:37,910 --> 00:49:39,110
By any chance...

637
00:49:39,720 --> 00:49:42,380
Could you tell me what Yoon Jae Uk's father's name was?

638
00:49:42,950 --> 00:49:44,290
One moment.

639
00:49:50,960 --> 00:49:54,830
His name was Yoon Dae Myeong. He passed away in 2003.

640
00:49:55,960 --> 00:49:57,630
But why do you ask?

641
00:49:58,400 --> 00:50:00,080
There's just something I have to find out.

642
00:50:01,440 --> 00:50:02,440
Thank you.

643
00:50:08,010 --> 00:50:10,650
(Pit-a-Pat Butcher Restaurant)

644
00:50:13,520 --> 00:50:14,880
(Yoon Dae Myeong)

645
00:50:22,890 --> 00:50:24,329
(Arrest warrant dismissed for Yoon Dae Myeong...)

646
00:50:24,330 --> 00:50:25,650
(over child molestation charges.)

647
00:50:29,700 --> 00:50:32,460
(Prosecutor Shin refiles warrant for Yoon in child molestation case.)

648
00:50:33,800 --> 00:50:34,999
(Yoon Dae Myeong's suicide sparks backlash...)

649
00:50:35,000 --> 00:50:36,280
(against excessive prosecution.)

650
00:50:37,940 --> 00:50:40,220
(Corrupt prosecutor Shin Gi Jung killed in car accident.)

651
00:50:40,610 --> 00:50:42,890
(Corrupt prosecutor Shin Gi Jung killed in car accident.)

652
00:50:58,290 --> 00:50:59,290
It's connected.

653
00:51:10,040 --> 00:51:11,640
Okay. Good work.

654
00:51:19,450 --> 00:51:22,420
I have to know what happened to protect your honour, Dad.

655
00:51:30,790 --> 00:51:33,800
(Recycling Guide)

656
00:51:56,720 --> 00:51:58,720
What are you doing here? Shouldn't you be home?

657
00:52:04,160 --> 00:52:06,060
I'm asking you, why are you out here like this?

658
00:52:09,900 --> 00:52:11,230
I want to know the truth.

659
00:52:14,000 --> 00:52:17,040
I've read all the articles, but I still don't understand.

660
00:52:22,110 --> 00:52:25,780
What happened to your father?

661
00:52:28,720 --> 00:52:32,350
And what did my father do?

662
00:52:33,390 --> 00:52:35,290
What's the point of digging all that up now?

663
00:52:37,330 --> 00:52:38,760
Whether it's your father or mine.

664
00:52:40,830 --> 00:52:42,130
They're both long gone.

665
00:52:44,430 --> 00:52:47,240
I still want to know.

666
00:52:48,470 --> 00:52:52,070
No, I need to know.

667
00:52:54,110 --> 00:52:55,110
Please.

668
00:53:06,090 --> 00:53:07,660
My father was an educator.

669
00:53:09,860 --> 00:53:12,830
He was a dedicated and respected teacher...

670
00:53:13,930 --> 00:53:16,330
who won Teacher of the Year 4 times in 25 years.

671
00:53:18,370 --> 00:53:21,670
But when he became vice principal, everything went wrong.

672
00:53:26,510 --> 00:53:28,640
There was a group bullying incident at the school,

673
00:53:30,050 --> 00:53:34,250
and my father made the tough call of expelling the student responsible.

674
00:53:34,380 --> 00:53:36,690
- One more time! - Good shot!

675
00:53:37,150 --> 00:53:41,790
The bully's parents sued my father, claiming it was excessive and biased,

676
00:53:42,960 --> 00:53:45,890
but the court threw it out and ruled in his favour.

677
00:53:48,400 --> 00:53:49,880
That's when the real trouble started.

678
00:53:51,600 --> 00:53:53,070
The prosecutor on the case,

679
00:53:55,140 --> 00:53:58,410
Prosecutor Shin Gi Jung, began a fishing expedition...

680
00:53:58,970 --> 00:54:01,710
and began indicting my father on completely unrelated charges.

681
00:54:06,010 --> 00:54:07,420
(Shin Gi Jung)

682
00:54:07,950 --> 00:54:08,950
Yes.

683
00:54:10,390 --> 00:54:11,590
All right, let's do that.

684
00:54:17,490 --> 00:54:21,100
He charged him for real estate speculation over a market gain,

685
00:54:27,240 --> 00:54:30,540
then charged him with embezzlement for a missing school meal receipt,

686
00:54:31,070 --> 00:54:33,030
(From Incheon District Court, To Yoon Dae Myeong)

687
00:54:35,340 --> 00:54:37,610
and even accused him of sexual harassment...

688
00:54:38,210 --> 00:54:40,020
for asking a student to fix their uniform.

689
00:54:40,420 --> 00:54:41,420
(Shin Gi Jung)

690
00:54:49,960 --> 00:54:51,590
Most of the charges were thrown out,

691
00:54:52,260 --> 00:54:55,760
but the legal battles kept my father from even going to work properly.

692
00:54:57,400 --> 00:54:58,730
And with the mounting legal fees,

693
00:55:00,470 --> 00:55:02,240
he lost the only home we had.

694
00:55:02,900 --> 00:55:05,310
But why would he go that far?

695
00:55:08,310 --> 00:55:13,150
Was there some kind of history between your father and mine?

696
00:55:13,750 --> 00:55:15,280
I wondered that myself,

697
00:55:17,290 --> 00:55:19,790
but it all made sense after I talked to our lawyer.

698
00:55:21,160 --> 00:55:26,090
He said it's common for ex-prosecutors to land cushy jobs at law firms.

699
00:55:28,360 --> 00:55:30,160
The father of the student who was expelled...

700
00:55:30,730 --> 00:55:32,770
was head of the country's top law firm.

701
00:55:35,200 --> 00:55:39,140
Prosecutor Shin Gi Jung used my father as a scapegoat.

702
00:55:40,410 --> 00:55:41,840
All for his own personal gain.

703
00:55:45,050 --> 00:55:47,250
He's the one who drove my father to his death.

704
00:55:58,060 --> 00:55:59,090
My father...

705
00:56:00,360 --> 00:56:03,500
was found dead in a back alley in Incheon's Chinatown.

706
00:56:04,970 --> 00:56:08,800
Half-burnt charcoal briquettes and a note were found in his car.

707
00:56:10,810 --> 00:56:12,610
The note had just one sentence written on it.

708
00:56:14,880 --> 00:56:15,940
To my family.

709
00:56:19,510 --> 00:56:20,650
I'm sorry.

710
00:56:25,390 --> 00:56:26,590
Then, three months later,

711
00:56:30,360 --> 00:56:32,290
my mother took her own life as well.

712
00:56:47,380 --> 00:56:48,580
All this time,

713
00:56:51,880 --> 00:56:54,120
I've completely turned a blind eye...

714
00:56:56,420 --> 00:56:57,920
to what my father did.

715
00:57:01,260 --> 00:57:04,360
I only thought of myself and my family as the victims.

716
00:57:08,230 --> 00:57:09,430
Now I realise...

717
00:57:12,730 --> 00:57:14,170
how incredibly selfish I've been.

718
00:57:16,570 --> 00:57:19,010
I had forgotten that so many were still suffering...

719
00:57:20,910 --> 00:57:22,010
due to it.

720
00:57:31,220 --> 00:57:35,060
I know an apology from me now won't change anything,

721
00:57:37,160 --> 00:57:40,730
but I am sincerely sorry.

722
00:58:07,160 --> 00:58:08,460
So, did you find the Shaman?

723
00:58:09,120 --> 00:58:11,920
I believe I'll be able to find him. Please give me a little more time.

724
00:58:13,230 --> 00:58:14,329
You need to hurry.

725
00:58:14,330 --> 00:58:19,000
If a shaman is summoning a ghost for Shin Yi Rang to meet,

726
00:58:21,770 --> 00:58:24,540
then that means he can meet that person too.

727
00:58:26,810 --> 00:58:27,810
That person?

728
00:58:59,010 --> 00:59:02,180
(Shin Yi Rang, Han Na Hyun Law Office)

729
00:59:08,450 --> 00:59:10,520
(Shin Yi Rang, Han Na Hyun Law Office)

730
00:59:34,380 --> 00:59:35,480
Who's there?

731
00:59:38,280 --> 00:59:39,850
What brings you here?

732
01:00:20,390 --> 01:00:22,220
I didn't mean to startle you.

733
01:00:23,460 --> 01:00:24,460
I apologise.

734
01:00:29,630 --> 01:00:31,870
- How... - I don't really know myself.

735
01:00:33,130 --> 01:00:36,270
Something drew me here.

736
01:00:38,640 --> 01:00:39,640
Why...

737
01:00:41,180 --> 01:00:42,180
now?

738
01:00:48,250 --> 01:00:49,450
It's too late.

739
01:00:50,250 --> 01:00:51,930
I'll come back first thing in the morning.

740
01:01:01,160 --> 01:01:02,260
I can't take this case.

741
01:01:05,770 --> 01:01:06,770
Excuse me?

742
01:01:06,771 --> 01:01:07,800
I...

743
01:01:11,910 --> 01:01:13,110
As for your case...

744
01:01:16,040 --> 01:01:17,210
I will not be taking it.

745
01:01:34,130 --> 01:01:36,490
(Special thanks to Choi Won Young for his guest appearance)

746
01:02:27,650 --> 01:02:32,290
(Phantom Lawyer)

747
01:02:32,490 --> 01:02:33,649
Is there a new ghost?

748
01:02:33,650 --> 01:02:35,566
It seems Yi Rang and that ghost don't get along.

749
01:02:35,590 --> 01:02:38,489
- I said, why now of all times? - Do you happen to know who I am?

750
01:02:38,490 --> 01:02:40,699
You are someone who can never be forgiven.

751
01:02:40,700 --> 01:02:43,129
Shin Gi Jung was the prosecutor on that case.

752
01:02:43,130 --> 01:02:45,376
It's late, but don't you think we should reveal the truth?

753
01:02:45,400 --> 01:02:48,539
I don't know who I am. All I know is that I'm dead.

754
01:02:48,540 --> 01:02:50,369
I'm calling because there's a ghost that needs to move on.

755
01:02:50,370 --> 01:02:53,270
- Was I that vicious? - So I'll have to send him on myself.

756
01:02:53,340 --> 01:02:54,780
- He's gone? - Yes, he's gone.

757
01:02:54,980 --> 01:02:56,240
Don't blame me.

